32275 32nd Ave S, Federal Way, Washington, 98001, United States of America

Responsible for Query Development, Testing and Quality Assurance; Interpret Business Requirements collected from Business Analysts and develop correct and efficient queries that comply with the team's definitions and standards; Create Technical Requirements and Metric Definition Documents; Interpret and Create Test Plans for Query and Report Development; Perform and Document Quality Assurance tasks for Query and Report Development; Troubleshoot and Research Issues in the reporting environment; Troubleshoot and maintain data integrity within our reporting environment; Develop maintain and troubleshoot ETL; Digest and maintain ERO and other diagrams describing the reporting environment; Perform Ad-Hoc Analysis, Data Mining & build forecasting models using Machine Learning techniques and statistical tools; Partner with developers throughout the department to promote consistency and efficiency; Partner with product owners to ensure data capture Is effective and reliable and create and maintain artifacts supporting Data Governance, Management, Delivery, and analysis;



The position requires minimum of a Master’s Degree in Information Systems or Computer Engineering or in related technical field and 24 months experience as Applications SQL Develop and/or Data Analyst to include experience in Healthcare IT; Data warehouse & data management; Building reports using Microsoft Access & Microsoft Excel, Tableau and in using Microsoft SQL Server to develop Advanced SQL queries, views, stored procedures and functions to support data analysts throughout the department; IBM SPSS Modeler & Python and ServiceNow.

Looking for a Data Architect to help lead data engineering team. This person should be able to lead the folks in the team in terms of task assignment, and also provide technical expertise in terms of data design and architecture, and also represent the team during discussions with the Data Science and Analytics teams.



ETL/DWH development - AWS (EMR/Redshift/Kinesis/Lambda/Glue/Athena),

Databases - Amazon Redshift, DynamoDB, PostgreSQL, Oracle 11g/12c, SQL Server;

Workload automation - AWS (Data Pipeline/CloudWatch/Step Functions), Rundeck/Airflow/Cron, Control-M 8.x;

DB Languages - PL/SQL, T-SQL, HiveQL;

Scripting - Unix /Linux Shell;

Programming: Java/scala

Data modeling - MySQL Workbench 6.3, ERwin 7, Visio 2007, Power Designer 12;

API formats - XML, JSON, YAML;

Version control - GitLab, SVN.
